{
  "texts": [
    "High user satisfaction is expected by closely addressing the diverse needs of users.",
    "The service market, exemplified by smartphone application stores, offers a vast array of services, enabling recommendations based on users' service usage histories [5,6].However, user needs are not always met through existing service recommendations, necessitating the development of new services to meet these requirements [7].",
    "However, the development of highly detailed services presents the challenge of increasing development costs.",
    "Additionally, it is inherently difficult to accurately capture user needs and develop services based on them.",
    "Even in previous research within software Sinan Chen, Sachio Saiki and Masahide Nakamura contributed equally to this work.engineering, automatically capturing users' active proposals for new services has not been successfully achieved."
  ]
}